to put me on the do not call list

1:11:02.429 --> 1:11:03.889
out of respect for her memory.

1:11:03.972 --> 1:11:05.557
-Right, son?
-That's right.

1:11:07.809 --> 1:11:09.311
You know, the head of the agency,

1:11:10.604 --> 1:11:14.441
the woman appointed by the goddamn
president of the United States,

1:11:14.525 --> 1:11:16.026
she called me personally.

1:11:17.528 --> 1:11:21.031
Personally, she swore to me,
up and down, left and right.

1:11:22.241 --> 1:11:25.953
"They will never call you again.
Not once, not twice, not ever."

1:11:31.166 --> 1:11:32.876
Guess I shoulda known better.

1:11:32.960 --> 1:11:34.753
Shouldn't have used
that DNC list, asshole.

1:11:40.133 --> 1:11:40.968
Dang it.

1:11:42.344 --> 1:11:44.054
Must've dozed off there.

1:11:44.137 --> 1:11:45.931
Oh, my God, I've never had to shit so bad.

1:11:50.727 --> 1:11:52.604
Wait. Did I miss something?

1:11:53.981 --> 1:11:57.568
-Quite a lot. Join our discussion.
-What's going on?

1:11:59.611 --> 1:12:00.988
You two work together, right?

1:12:01.947 --> 1:12:03.574
-Yeah.
-Know why he's here?

1:12:05.701 --> 1:12:08.495
I figured he stayed behind
to try to make another call.

1:12:08.579 --> 1:12:09.788
And if he made it,

1:12:09.872 --> 1:12:13.041
he would report it
to corporate claiming...

1:12:14.835 --> 1:12:17.421
-he won the $3,000.
-Bingo.

1:12:19.298 --> 1:12:21.091
Must make your blood boil, right?

1:12:22.885 --> 1:12:25.179
-No.
-No?

1:12:26.597 --> 1:12:31.185
No. Actually, I feel relieved.

1:12:32.186 --> 1:12:35.564
I don't feel so bad about
switching his call sheet with Justin's.

1:12:38.108 --> 1:12:39.026
You did what?

1:12:40.319 --> 1:12:42.654
Hold on. So let me get this straight.

1:12:43.530 --> 1:12:46.116
You cheat, and then all this happens?

1:12:47.576 --> 1:12:49.536
You have no idea
what I've been through today!

1:12:49.620 --> 1:12:54.333
Law of the land. Remember?
All I did was level the playing field.

1:12:54.416 --> 1:12:58.795
And you have no position to be
calling anybody in here unethical

1:12:58.879 --> 1:13:02.007
when you're the one who got kicked out
of USC's law school for cheating.

1:13:02.090 --> 1:13:04.301
Oh, my God,
I've been wanting to say that all day.

1:13:05.010 --> 1:13:05.886
Oh, my God.

1:13:06.845 --> 1:13:08.639
Say it isn't so.

1:13:10.057 --> 1:13:11.725
I mean, he's drunk.

1:13:11.808 --> 1:13:13.435
I know all about it, okay?

1:13:13.519 --> 1:13:16.647
Your assistant dean, she told me about it.
We're in the same church choir.

1:13:16.730 --> 1:13:18.565
And the church says amen.

1:13:18.649 --> 1:13:22.194
-You told me you dropped out.
-Baby, I'm-- Thank you.

1:13:22.986 --> 1:13:24.279
Thank you very much, Barry.

1:13:25.322 --> 1:13:27.741
Kasey, your buddy just sold you out.

1:13:29.326 --> 1:13:31.245
-Hey, pops.
-Yeah, son?

1:13:31.328 --> 1:13:33.872
What were you telling me about deterrence?

1:13:33.956 --> 1:13:35.541
Deterrence theory.

1:13:35.624 --> 1:13:37.042
Deterrence theory, yeah.

1:13:38.418 --> 1:13:41.505
Barry, I learned something today.

1:13:41.588 --> 1:13:46.176
The use of extreme actions to prevent
the reoccurrence of a specific action.

1:13:46.260 --> 1:13:48.262
-Spot-on, son.
-Yeah.

1:13:48.762 --> 1:13:52.099
Kasey, do you know the one thing
I detest more than telemarketers?

1:13:53.934 --> 1:13:54.768
A snitch?

1:13:56.103 --> 1:13:57.396
Gold star for you.

1:13:59.773 --> 1:14:00.983
Fuck me!

1:14:01.066 --> 1:14:02.609
What the fuck, man!

1:14:03.318 --> 1:14:04.570
Oh, my God!

1:14:05.612 --> 1:14:08.240
You know, that's a clean hole.

1:14:10.951 --> 1:14:13.078
Would you go clean that up for us?

1:14:13.996 --> 1:14:15.122
-Me?
-Yes, please.

1:14:16.540 --> 1:14:18.584
Go on over. Go on, clean it up.

1:14:21.753 --> 1:14:23.046
Grab the...

1:14:23.964 --> 1:14:24.965
Yeah, grab the...

1:14:30.971 --> 1:14:32.431
How long do you think he's got?

1:14:32.514 --> 1:14:36.560
I don't know. I mean, I'm trying to be
a psychologist, not a doctor.

1:14:36.643 --> 1:14:40.189
-Put your hands on it. Yeah.
-Isn't this perfect?

1:14:40.272 --> 1:14:43.358
Now, his life is in your hands.

1:14:43.442 --> 1:14:46.695
Okay, look,
just let Barry and Christine go. Okay?

1:14:47.821 --> 1:14:50.532
You can lock me in your basement,
give me your phone.

1:14:50.616 --> 1:14:53.285
I'll make as many calls as you want,
apologise to as many people

1:14:53.368 --> 1:14:57.664
-as you want for the rest of my life.
-Now, that would be going too far.

1:14:57.748 --> 1:15:02.044
I mean, plus the train set's down there,
and Dean's man cave.

1:15:02.127 --> 1:15:05.422
-Yeah.
-All we need is one apology accepted.

1:15:06.131 --> 1:15:09.051
Here, now, for all to hear. Now, come on.

1:15:10.093 --> 1:15:13.430
Go on, just get your do not call list,

1:15:13.514 --> 1:15:18.602
and you best get to dialling
before you all get clocked out.

1:15:19.228 --> 1:15:20.062
Okay.

1:15:20.562 --> 1:15:23.482
Seeing as how this
could potentially be my very last call...

1:15:25.317 --> 1:15:27.986
-I'm gonna need a cup of coffee.
-No.

1:15:28.070 --> 1:15:31.865
Hey, now.
It's my pre last call ritual, you know.

1:15:32.491 --> 1:15:34.493
Every time I make my final call,

1:15:35.035 --> 1:15:40.457
I need to have one cup of coffee
from my signature toilet bowl mug.

1:15:41.333 --> 1:15:43.001
Ain't that right, rookie?

1:15:43.085 --> 1:15:45.087
Yeah, as long as I've been here.

1:15:45.629 --> 1:15:47.005
-Oh, Christ.
-Stop.

1:15:47.506 --> 1:15:48.340
Jesus Christ.

1:15:48.423 --> 1:15:49.258
Yeah.

1:15:51.009 --> 1:15:52.803
Why don't you get the fucking coffee?

1:15:54.847 --> 1:15:57.558
You don't strike me as someone
who would drink out of the toilet.

1:15:58.267 --> 1:16:00.435
I mean, he's full of shit, so...

1:16:00.519 --> 1:16:03.647
You know, I tried it once,
sold a triple play,

1:16:03.730 --> 1:16:05.607
so I'm not one to argue with success.

1:16:05.691 --> 1:16:09.987
Here's your goddamn coffee.
Go ahead, take your ritualistic sip.

1:16:12.739 --> 1:16:15.909
This here is your last call.

1:16:17.619 --> 1:16:21.665
If this doesn't work, you're going
on a boat ride with me and Dean.

1:16:23.333 --> 1:16:24.168
Dial.

1:16:42.436 --> 1:16:43.270
Yes?

1:16:44.688 --> 1:16:46.064
Hello, sir, it's Kasey.

1:16:48.358 --> 1:16:49.234
Yes, Kasey?

1:16:49.902 --> 1:16:52.321
It's late, I'm surprised you're still up.

1:16:53.739 --> 1:16:56.450
-Just reading some motions.
-Of course you are.

1:16:58.744 --> 1:16:59.745
Did you need something?

1:17:02.289 --> 1:17:03.415
Yeah, I was just...

1:17:05.417 --> 1:17:06.752
You know, I've been...

1:17:08.045 --> 1:17:10.547
just been meaning
to talk to you, you know.

1:17:11.882 --> 1:17:13.884
I already got Internet, thank you.

1:17:14.510 --> 1:17:16.011
Okay, yeah, I guess I deserve that.

1:17:16.678 --> 1:17:20.641
But no, there's something I've been
meaning to speak with you about.

1:17:22.059 --> 1:17:23.602
I got cable and phone too.

1:17:23.685 --> 1:17:26.730
I'm not... Look, sir, I'm not selling.

1:17:27.272 --> 1:17:28.815
I didn't know that was possible.

1:17:28.899 --> 1:17:33.654
Sir, please, I just wanted to apologise.

1:17:35.197 --> 1:17:37.741
-I didn't know that was possible either.
-Come on.

1:17:39.493 --> 1:17:40.994
Go on, I'm listening.

1:17:41.078 --> 1:17:42.621
I just wanted to say...

1:17:46.166 --> 1:17:47.042
I'm sorry.

1:17:48.877 --> 1:17:51.296
I'm sorry for this dirty business I'm in.

1:17:52.965 --> 1:17:55.175
And the pain it must cause people.

1:17:57.135 --> 1:17:58.136
And that includes you.

1:17:59.972 --> 1:18:01.682
I guess when you think about it, I just,

1:18:02.391 --> 1:18:04.226
was never really good
at anything, you know?

1:18:05.060 --> 1:18:08.689
Sports, school, none of it.

1:18:10.941 --> 1:18:12.234
But here, I'm good.

1:18:13.277 --> 1:18:14.695
I'm real good, you know?

1:18:15.946 --> 1:18:17.197
I can do what I want,

1:18:17.823 --> 1:18:20.409
can come and go as I please,
and nobody calls me out on it.

1:18:21.702 --> 1:18:23.287
Almost no one.

1:18:24.538 --> 1:18:26.498
Compared to law school,
this place is amazing.

1:18:27.165 --> 1:18:28.375
You see, in class...

1:18:29.501 --> 1:18:32.379
In class I would just lie
and cheat my way through everything.

1:18:32.462 --> 1:18:36.508
And it worked for a little while,
but then you get kicked out.

1:18:38.468 --> 1:18:39.970
And then you end up here.

1:18:42.556 --> 1:18:46.351
You see, here I can meet people,

1:18:47.811 --> 1:18:48.979
I get to know them,

1:18:50.522 --> 1:18:52.900
and right when I got them
where I want them, I sell them.

1:18:53.567 --> 1:18:55.736
And I sell them, and I sell them.

1:18:56.320 --> 1:18:57.988
The bullshit works.

1:18:58.071 --> 1:19:01.074
It works here.
In fact, they encourage it, you know?

1:19:01.158 --> 1:19:02.868
So much so that corporate, you know,

1:19:02.951 --> 1:19:05.120
corporate is starting
to call it the Kasey Method.

1:19:05.204 --> 1:19:06.205
Can you believe that?

1:19:06.288 --> 1:19:09.082
They named something after me,
the Kasey Method.

1:19:10.000 --> 1:19:13.962
I lie and I cheat people,
and they pat me on the back for it.

1:19:15.255 --> 1:19:17.049
I don't like me because of it.

1:19:19.635 --> 1:19:21.553
And I know
I'm not the man you want me to be,

1:19:22.763 --> 1:19:24.890
I didn't go down the path
you wanted me to go down.

1:19:29.061 --> 1:19:30.354
For that, I'm sorry.

1:19:31.230 --> 1:19:33.190
I truly am, I am very sorry.

1:19:37.319 --> 1:19:38.153
So...

1:19:40.030 --> 1:19:40.989
what do you say?

1:19:43.325 --> 1:19:46.078
Do you accept my apology, Dad?

1:19:51.250 --> 1:19:54.795
Oh, and there's somebody
I would really like for you to meet.

1:19:54.878 --> 1:19:57.714
So, depending on your answer,
I think we should all hang out.

1:19:57.798 --> 1:19:59.633
I think you would
really like her, you know?

1:20:05.347 --> 1:20:09.268
You know, son,
I'm really happy you called.

1:20:11.687 --> 1:20:13.105
Of course I forgive you.

1:20:22.614 --> 1:20:23.448
No!

1:20:43.635 --> 1:20:45.762
Baby, call 911. Call 911, right now!

1:20:45.846 --> 1:20:47.472
No!

1:20:47.556 --> 1:20:49.183
I'm not going back to jail!

1:20:50.142 --> 1:20:51.643
Shut up, you goddamn...

1:20:54.062 --> 1:20:56.607
-Thanks for the mug, rookie.
-I try.

1:20:58.400 --> 1:20:59.693
Since we're in apologies mode,

1:20:59.776 --> 1:21:02.029
I'm sorry there's a hole
in your leg right now.

1:21:03.780 --> 1:21:06.116
It's not your fault, it's his.

1:21:07.492 --> 1:21:09.703
Oh, no, please, I'm sorry. I'm sorry!

1:21:11.705 --> 1:21:12.664
Oh, shit!

1:21:14.291 --> 1:21:15.667
Apology accepted.

1:21:17.920 --> 1:21:21.924
Baby, I'm sorry I'm an asshole.
I'm sorry I stood you up, you know?

1:21:22.007 --> 1:21:23.967
-I'm sorry.
-We can do this later.

1:21:24.051 --> 1:21:26.845
Apologies all around.
Everybody gets an apology.

1:21:26.929 --> 1:21:30.474
I too am sorry for not
shooting you in the goddamn head

1:21:30.557 --> 1:21:33.018
when I first laid eyes on you.

1:21:37.397 --> 1:21:38.273
Hold this.

1:21:41.693 --> 1:21:42.528
Asa.

1:21:43.987 --> 1:21:45.572
I know you got a raw deal.

1:21:46.448 --> 1:21:47.699
Losing the love of your life,

1:21:48.450 --> 1:21:51.662
and how that must be
affecting you and Dean.

1:21:53.247 --> 1:21:55.791
I'm not gonna pretend to imagine
what that must feel like.

1:21:55.874 --> 1:21:57.918
And if I could go back in time,

1:21:58.001 --> 1:22:00.546
I would really change
your circumstance, man, I really would.

1:22:02.381 --> 1:22:04.508
I'm sad about your wife, Asa,

1:22:04.591 --> 1:22:08.804
and the role this fucked-up
telemarketing culture played in it.

1:22:10.848 --> 1:22:13.767
Damn it, Asa, I'm sorry, man. I really am.

1:22:16.144 --> 1:22:17.271
Kasey Miller.

1:22:18.355 --> 1:22:20.357
That's all I ever wanted from you.

1:22:21.483 --> 1:22:26.196
Was for you to take a good,
deep, long look at yourself.

1:22:28.615 --> 1:22:29.950
I know it wasn't easy.

1:22:32.452 --> 1:22:33.453
I'm proud of you.

1:22:35.289 --> 1:22:37.165
I'm gonna accept your apology.

1:22:38.208 --> 1:22:39.042
I do.

1:22:42.004 --> 1:22:44.131
It still wasn't on the phone though.

1:22:45.716 --> 1:22:48.218
-You've got to be kidding me.
-Come on, I'm dying over here.

1:22:48.302 --> 1:22:50.846
-Let's get you taken care of.
-Take this, I don't want this.

1:22:50.929 --> 1:22:51.972
-You sure?
-Yes.

1:22:52.055 --> 1:22:54.725
-Because I can kill them right now.
-What? No.

1:22:54.808 --> 1:22:57.102
I'm just saying,
he's been talking so much shit.

1:23:12.326 --> 1:23:13.285
That's a pretty house.

1:23:15.287 --> 1:23:16.121
Are you okay?

1:23:19.082 --> 1:23:20.459
No, I'm good. I just...

1:23:22.002 --> 1:23:22.836
I just...

1:23:24.713 --> 1:23:26.215
It doesn't feel right, you know?

1:23:27.007 --> 1:23:30.427
-Yeah, but you wanted to do this.
